comments[4]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-07-23T15:06:24.649Z",claude-code-agent,"Duplicate check 2026-07-23: all-status search for renderer ownership and doctor found only closed pmc-nagj, which introduced the unscoped JSON renderer behavior; this task is its non-duplicative SDK migration."
  "2026-07-23T15:07:50.380Z",claude-code-agent,"Implementation checkpoint: toon/json registrations now share host-enforced ownership for changelog generate/export plus a RenderedCommandResult discriminator. Local pm-cli SDK typecheck/build and the focused extension suite pass; full package and isolated installed-doctor acceptance waits for the pm-cli scoped-renderer release."
  "2026-07-23T16:41:41.998Z",claude-code-agent,"Dependency boundary: npm pm-cli 2026.7.23 predates scoped renderer ownership, while merged main 9b079a56 contains the reviewed contract. The package now declares pm >=2026.7.24 and pins its development SDK to that exact merged commit so CI validates the real contract without falsely claiming the current registry version supports it."
  "2026-07-23T16:45:03.965Z",claude-code-agent,"Correction to dependency checkpoint: a Git source dependency was rejected because npm does not run pm-cli's prepublish build and therefore exposes no dist SDK. The committed lock remains on published 2026.7.23 for backward type compilation via an exact local compatibility signature copied from merged SDK types; peer/manifest require 2026.7.24, and full installed-doctor acceptance remains deliberately blocked until that daily release exists. Focused build, 6 extension contract tests, zero-vulnerability production audit, and 37-file pack dry-run pass."
